@Toc "Main"

Avancť
******

   Il y a dans Charon v1.98, quelques nouvelles options inaccessibles au
travers de l'interface graphique :

   @{b}*@{ub} Charon a deux types d'outils/arguments CLI, @{b}Settings@{ub} et @{b}LOG@{ub}. le
     type d'outils @{b}Settings@{ub} indique ŗ Charon la configuration ŗ
     charger ŗ la place de @{b}PROGDIR:Charon.cfg@{ub}.  Le type d'outils @{b}LOG@{ub}
     indique le nom du fichier journal dans lequel Charon enregistrera
     les ťvťnements. Si li n'y a pas d'argument de donnť, le fichier
     par dťfaut ressemblera ŗ quelque chose comme :
     @{b}T:Charon.debug.xxxxxxxx@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Si un fichier nommť PROGDIR:Config/HTTPHeadersLog existe, Charon
     lira la premiŤre ligne de ce fichier pour obtenir le nom du
     fichier dans lequel il ťcrira toutes les en-tÍtes HTTP qui
     envoie et reÁoit.  Cela pourraÓt Ítre quelque chose comme
     CON:... Cette option sert essentiellement au dťbogage.

   @{b}*@{ub} Si un fichier nommť PROGDIR:Config/NoFilesizeCheck existe, Charon
     ne vťrifiera pas la taille de chaque fichier durant le dťmarrage.
     Ceci est utile lorsque vous avez une trŤs grosse liste et que
     lire la taille des fichiers prendrait trop de temps. Toutefois, si
     cette option est utilisťe la taille du fichier sur le serveur ne
     sera pas affichťe (l'information de pourcentage serait fausse).


@EndNode

@Node "Trucs et astuces" "Charon.guide/Trucs et astuces"
@Next "Historique"
@Prev "Avancť"
@Toc "Main"

Trucs et astuces
****************

   @{b}*@{ub} Les entrťes dans la liste principale peuvent se dťplacer ŗ
     l'aide de la souris. Vous pouvez les dťplacer et changer l'ordre
     des tťlťchargements et des groupes comme il vous plaira.

   @{b}*@{ub} Vous recherchez un fichier MP3 ? Utilisez la fenÍtre de recherche
     sur Internet !

   @{b}*@{ub} Si vous utilisez AWeb et que vous souhaitez rťcupťrer les liens
     d'une page, utilisez le script ARexx ShowLinks.rexx pour qu'ils
     s'affichent.

   @{b}*@{ub} La fenÍtre d'ťdition d'une URL est une ę app-window Ľ.  Vous
     pouvez y dťposer des icŰnes et Charon utilisera les noms de ces
     fichiers.  Si le fichier a une URL dans le champ de commentaire,
     ce commentaire sera copiť dans le champ de l'URL.

   @{b}*@{ub} La fenÍtre d'ťdition de l'URL possŤde un menu qui vous permet de
     charger un fichier @{b}.cfg@{ub}. Vous pouvez crťer un fichier @{b}.cfg@{ub} si
     vous choisissez @{b}Sauver rťglages sous...@{ub} ŗ partir du menu
     Rťglages.

   @{b}*@{ub} Quand vous ťditez une URL dans la fenÍtre d'ťdition, pressez
     @{b}entrer@{ub} pour que Charon crťe automatiquement le nom de fichier ŗ
     partir de l'URL.

   @{b}*@{ub} Utilisez le script ARexx fourni pour envoyer les liens d'un
     navigateur vers Charon.

        @{b}*@{ub} Dans AWeb, allez dans Rťglages/GUI Rťglages/contextuel et
          ajoutez une entrťe pour chaque type.  Le nom de la commande
          peut Ítre par exemple @{b}Tťlťchargement@{ub} et la commande serait
          @{b}SYSTEM CharonPath:Rexx/AddURL.rexx "%u"@{ub}. Ceci tťlťchargera
          les fichiers dans votre rťpertoire de tťlťchargement par
          dťfaut.

        @{b}*@{ub} Dans IBrowse 2.2+, allez dans le menu
          Rťglages/Rťglages.../GUI/FAB, puis dťposez une entrťe
          customisťe pour chaque lien dans les sections, Image-liens,
          Page et Image (Vous pouvez alors les renommer comme bon vous
          semble. Sťlectionnez ARexx dans le gadget cyclique et
          choisissez le script AddURL.rexx. Dans le champ d'arguments,
          mettre "%i", "%l" ou "%u" pour tťlťcharger respectivement
          une image, un liens ou une page.

        @{b}*@{ub} D'aussi loin que je me souvienne, cette fonctionnalitť
          devraÓt Ítre disponible dans Voyager, mais je n'en connais
          pas les dťtails.


@EndNode

@Node "Historique" "Charon.guide/Historique"
@Next "Support"
@Prev "Trucs et astuces"
@Toc "Main"

Historique
**********

   [Volontairement non-traduit]
@{b}Version 1.98 (6.1.2002)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} Introduced the concept of groups. Now each URL can belong to
          a group and will take that group's Rťglages as its default
          Rťglages. A new URL is by default placed in the group in
          which the active entry indicator is currently found.

        @{b}*@{ub} Completely rewritten URL parsing routine which resulted in a
          large speed up. This speed up would be even larger, but the
          URL comparison routine was changed from simple string compare
          to full-blown URL comparison routine which works properly.

        @{b}*@{ub} Rewritten detection of duplicates in the list. The code is now
          much faster and works for any number of duplicates, unlike in
          the last version.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now remembers the length of the file on server and
          shows it all the time (if it is available).

        @{b}*@{ub} Many improvements and some fixes in the HTML parsing routine.

        @{b}*@{ub} Addressed some security issues.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's now a special treatment for %2F URL escape code (/)
          because there are some filesystems that allow / in a filename.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added support for ftp://.../file;type=x URLs.

        @{b}*@{ub} When automatically creating filenames from the URL, %xx
          sequences are now decoded.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's a @{"new section" Link "Avancť"} in the documentation describing some
          "hidden" features. Charon's tooltypes/arguments (@{b}LOG@{ub} and
          @{b}Rťglages@{ub}) are documented there.

        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to log all HTTP headers that were sent or
          received through Charon for debugging purposes. More about
          this in the @{"Avancť section" Link "Avancť"} of the manual.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's a new configuration option which tells Charon not to
          read the size of the files on the disk during the startup thus
          speeding it up. More about this in the @{"Avancť section" Link "Avancť"} of
          the manual.

        @{b}*@{ub} DOS requesters are now blocked while the list of entries is
          being loaded in order to prevent a bunch of the "Please
          insert ..." requesters from a appearing if one of your drives
          is dismounted.

        @{b}*@{ub} New gadget "Move & start" in HTML links and Internet search
          windows.

        @{b}*@{ub} Changed the way Charon shortens the filenames when "Max
          filename length" option comes into action.

        @{b}*@{ub} Changed the way the ę Directory structure Ľ option works.
          It now also takes into consideration the name of the host.

        @{b}*@{ub} When a file is downloaded and Charon needs to check if there
          are any queued files to be started, they are first searched
          for in the same group in which the downloaded file was.

        @{b}*@{ub} Some changes in Interface ARexx as a result of introduction
          of groups.

        @{b}*@{ub} Updated some and removed some searches from Internet search
          window.  Ideas for possible additions are welcome.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a bug in parsing dates in HTTP headers.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a rare bug in display of percentage of the downloaded
          file.

        @{b}*@{ub} Too long FTP paths would cause a crash while sending a
          request. Fixed.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a small memory leak during that occured only when Charon
          was started from the shell.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon would report that it couldn't resume a transfer when a
          file had already been downloaded fully.

        @{b}*@{ub} SET Arexx command wasn't working properly for ages, fixed.

@{b}Version 1.4 (31.7.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} Double click on an entry now starts downloading it
          immediately, regardless of "Maximum transfers" option (it
          acted just the same as "Start" button up to now).

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon sometimes wouldn't resolve numeric IP addresses
          properly.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added a gadget next to "Proxy" gadget which lists all proxies
          from "Proxies" page in Rťglages window making it easy to set
          current proxy to one of those.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added few more error messages that better explain what went
          wrong while connecting to a host.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added workaround for some servers (or scripts) which send
          relative URLs in Location: header for redirection although
          HTTP standard specifically says that they have to be absolute.

        @{b}*@{ub} While working on the above problem, fixed a much worse bug in
          handling Location: headers that could even cause a crash.

        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to log into FTP servers which send their
          initial greeting using somewhat unusual (although perfectly
          legal) multiline response.

        @{b}*@{ub} HTML links parser erroneously treated "./" as "../"

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed display of remaining time (it actually showed total
          length of the transfer). If I find another bug connected to
          this, I will have to seriously consider becoming a circus
          clown.

        @{b}*@{ub} Most of numeric buttons in Rťglages window have been changed
          to a special kind of numeric string gadgets. They allow input
          of numbers only in certain range and have bubble help to
          indicate which range is that.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option: "Always find proxy" tells Charon to always try to
          set the proxy based on your current IP address, not only when
          you create an entry for the first time.

        @{b}*@{ub} Del key is now shortcut for "Remove".

        @{b}*@{ub} HTML parser now ignores mailto: links.

        @{b}*@{ub} Active downloads window didn't update data percentage properly
          when the main window was hidden.

        @{b}*@{ub} Now removes "blah" out of http://www.host.com/file.html#blah
          user entered URLs (which it should have been doing since ages
          ago, argh).

        @{b}*@{ub} If "Directory structure" option is active (ie. it's not set to
          -1) and filename contains just name of directory, Charon will
          append index.html to it.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu item and ARexx option: "Export list over" which
          overwrites the file to which it writes the list instead of
          appending to it.

        @{b}*@{ub} Removed some space between Rťglages pages and save/use/cancel
          gadgets in Rťglages window which sometimes caused MUI to
          render it in a rather strange way.

        @{b}*@{ub} Moved "No proxy" gadget to Local1 page, next to "Proxy"
          gadget.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now sets busy pointer whenever a list is loaded or
          saved.

        @{b}*@{ub} Corrected spelling of ARexx command TRANSFEREDLENGTH to
          TRANSFERREDLENGTH. The old form is still accepted for
          compatibility rasons.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added SETAUTHORISATION as synonym for SETAUTHORIZATION ARexx
          command.

        @{b}*@{ub} Bubble help for main display which showed URL, proxy and
          percentage of an entry is now updated more regularly.

@{b}Version 1.3 (24.6.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} New option: Edit script. When you edit an entry in edit window
          and click OK or OK & start, this script will be called so you
          can change something in the entry (for example, set
          username/password, change proxy).

        @{b}*@{ub} Files from Backup directory are now automatically imported
          into Charon's main list.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed display of sizes/transfer rates of extremely large files
          (hopefuly for the last time).

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed crashes when changing Internet search engine. There was
          something really strange about this, I still think there was
          nothing wrong with Charon. Anyway, the fix definitely works.

        @{b}*@{ub} If server sends larger file than it indicated, Charon now acts
          as if no size was specified. This fixes problems with some bad
          servers.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a pretty big bug: if the last entry in the list was
          selected and second entry from the end active, the whole list
          would be deleted!

        @{b}*@{ub} Faster adding of links from Internet search and HTML links
          window to main window.

        @{b}*@{ub} If an entry was downloading and was removed, queued file(s)
          that should have been started wouldn't be started.

        @{b}*@{ub} Made it impossible for older versions of Charon to open
          libraries of newer versions (since these are incompatible)
          just in case.

        @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Select none@{ub} menu entry and ARexx command now also turn off
          the active entry.

        @{b}*@{ub} New ARexx command: SETAUTHORIZATION which sets username and
          password in a URL.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added an ARexx script to "pause" (actually to stop and then
          start) downloads until you, for example, collect your e-mail
          or something similar.

        @{b}*@{ub} Internal cleanups.

@{b}Version 1.2 (19.4.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to hide only main window and leave other
          windows open, f. ex. active downloads window.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option to make close window gadget act as iconify command.

        @{b}*@{ub} Finally properly fixed time remaining indicator.

        @{b}*@{ub} Somewhat undocumented tooltype/argument DEBUG has been changed
          to LOG which now optionally logs almost everything that
          happens while URL is downloaded.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed two bugs in HTML parsing, one of the two could be quite
          fatal at times (luckily, it would rarely happen).

        @{b}*@{ub} New ARexx command BACKUP which forces immediate backup of the
          list file.

        @{b}*@{ub} QUERY ARexx command now has two new arguments:
          TRANSFEREDLENGTH and FULLLENGTH.

@{b}Version 1.1 (24.3.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} New window for Internet searches. Currently, Aminet,
          AudioFind, MP3Box, Lycos MP3Search and Lycos FTPSearch
          searches are supported, but more searches are easy to add.

        @{b}*@{ub} New window which extracts all links from HTML file.

        @{b}*@{ub} New window that logs finished downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} New window that shows only active downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} New "minimal information" window that shows some info about
          the list of downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now optionally backs up its download list every x
          minutes.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option to execute a command when Charon is started and
          when it exits.

        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to execute a command before the download
          is started and after it's finished.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option: rollback which tries to prevent bad proxies from
          mangling the file which is being downloaded.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's a new option to make Charon show only filename part
          of the URL. This option is also accessible from the display's
          context menu.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now visually indicates when an entry with the same
          filename is entered.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu entry: stop started downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu entries which make it possible to select all, toggle
          selected, select started entries. These options are also
          accessible from the display's context menu.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu entry: New clipboard URL.

        @{b}*@{ub} New "paste from clipboard" gadget in edit window for those
          who are used to HTTPResume.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now uses Textinput MUI custom class by Oliver Wagner
          (if it's available) for its string gadgets.

        @{b}*@{ub} Corrected a problem which appeared when downloading from
          wu-ftpd-2.6.x FTP server.

        @{b}*@{ub} Edit window now has "OK & start" gadget.

        @{b}*@{ub} Bubble help for main list now gives some information about
          the currently active entry. This information is updated only
          when active entry is changed!

        @{b}*@{ub} Main window is now also an app window. It is also possible to
          drop icons on Charon's app icon when it's iconified.

        @{b}*@{ub} Width of the main list is now saved only on a window snapshot.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed the way time to end of the download was calculated.

        @{b}*@{ub} Rťglages window is rearranged.

        @{b}*@{ub} NEWURL ARexx command has new special URL called "clipboard"
          which gets it from the clipboard.

        @{b}*@{ub} Included ARexx example how to change an option for all
          selected URLs.

        @{b}*@{ub} Included ARexx script which shows all links on current HTML
          page in AWeb. Useful if you are on a ROM or picture gallery
          site and you want to download some links.

        @{b}*@{ub} ARexx commands are updated with new options.

@{b}Version 1.0 (3.2.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} 1ere version diffusťe au public.


@EndNode

